A Senegalese UN soldier was killed by shrapnel  when a shell landed close to his car in central Kigali on Tuesday, a UN  military officer said.
The soldier was killed near a checkpoint, manned by government forces, by  a shell believed to have been fired by the rebel Rwandan Patriotic Front, said  UN force deputy commander Brigadier Henry Anyidoho.
His body was taken to Kigali airport.
The driver's seat in the car was covered in blood, an AFP reporter on the  scene of the attack said.
